<p>This document provides a detailed technical specification of the DETR (D=
Etection TRansformer) architecture used in GigaCheck for character-level in=
terval detection of AI-generated text. The DETR model identifies precise ch=
aracter intervals within mixed human-AI documents.</p>
<p>For information about the classification model architecture, see <a href=
=3D"https://deepwiki.com/ai-forever/gigacheck/5.2-classification-head-and-l=
ora" class=3D"text-neutral-300 hover:text-neutral-200 hover:underline">Clas=
sification Head and LoRA</a>. For training procedures, see <a href=3D"https=
://deepwiki.com/ai-forever/gigacheck/4.2-detection-model-training" class=3D=
"text-neutral-300 hover:text-neutral-200 hover:underline">Detection Model T=
raining</a>. For the base Mistral model integration, see <a href=3D"https:/=
/deepwiki.com/ai-forever/gigacheck/5.1-mistral-base-model" class=3D"text-ne=
utral-300 hover:text-neutral-200 hover:underline">Mistral Base Model</a>.</=
p>
