<p>The GigaCheck detection system adapts DETR=E2=80=94originally designed f=
or 2D object detection in images=E2=80=94to 1D interval detection in text s=
equences. Instead of predicting bounding boxes around objects, the model pr=
edicts character intervals marking AI-generated spans.</p>
<p>The architecture consists of:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Transformer Encoder</strong>: Processes contextualized token em=
beddings from Mistral-7B</li>
<li><strong>Transformer Decoder</strong>: Refines a fixed set of learnable =
object queries</li>
<li><strong>Object Queries</strong>: 45 learnable embeddings that each pred=
ict one AI-generated interval</li>
<li><strong>Hungarian Matcher</strong>: Bipartite matching algorithm for tr=
aining supervision</li>
<li><strong>Multi-task Loss</strong>: Combines span localization, GIoU, and=
 classification losses</li>
</ul>
<p>The model supports two DETR variants:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>DAB-DETR</strong>: Anchor-based queries with dynamic initializa=
tion</li>
<li><strong>DN-DETR</strong>: Adds denoising training for improved robustne=
ss</li>
</ul>
